DATA SCIENCE
##
- "Big Data" is a huge market (est. 40% yearly growth to ~$17B in 2015)
- Applications across many different industries
- All depends on people doing math
- Useful skills: statistics, AI, R, Mathematica





















##
PERSISTENT HOMOLOGY
##
- Applied algebraic topology
- View data points as living inside some high dimensional metric space
- Use algebraic topology to study the shape of data sets to find important features
- Ayasdi - SV startup founded by G. Carlsson





















##
CATEGORY THEORY
- Functional programming is a popular movement towards mathematical functions and composition
- Many applications from category theory and algebra: monads, functors, monoids, comonads, ...
- Haskell in particular is strongly grounded in mathematical formalism, but gaining traction in industry
##





















##
HOMOTOPY TYPE THEORY
- New foundational system based on type theory and based loosely on the metaphor:
  type  : space
  proof : point
  =     : path
- Constructive proofs
- Strong applicability to automated proof assistants
- Developed collaboratively using Git
